
== Preparation

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large #pan{} over medium heat.

Add @onion{1%medium, diced} and @garlic{3%cloves, minced} to the pan. Cook for ~{3%minutes} until softened.

<meat> Add @ground beef{500%g} and cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon, about ~{5%minutes}.
| <vegetarian> Add @mushrooms{250%g, chopped} and @walnuts{100%g, chopped} and cook for ~{5%minutes} until mushrooms are browned.
| <vegan> Add @lentils{200%g, cooked} and @mushrooms{250%g, chopped} and cook for ~{5%minutes} until heated through.

+<spicy> Add @red pepper flakes{1%tsp} and stir for ~{30%seconds}.

Add @tomato paste{2%tbsp} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in @crushed tomatoes{400%g, canned} and @red wine{125%ml}.

+<herbs> Add @fresh basil{2%tbsp, chopped} and @oregano{1%tsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} to taste.

== Cooking

Bring the sauce to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for ~{30%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

+<rich> Stir in @heavy cream{100%ml} during the last ~{5%minutes} of cooking.

Meanwhile, bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Add @spaghetti{400%g} and cook according to package directions until al dente, about ~{8-10%minutes}.

+<extra-cheese> Reserve @pasta water{1%cup} before draining.

Drain the pasta and return to the pot.

== Serving

Toss the pasta with the sauce.

+<extra-cheese> Add @parmesan cheese{100%g, grated} and a splash of the reserved pasta water. Toss until creamy.

<meat> Serve immediately topped with @parmesan cheese{50%g, grated}.
| <vegetarian> Serve immediately topped with @parmesan cheese{50%g, grated}.
| <vegan> Serve immediately topped with @nutritional yeast{3%tbsp}.

+<garnish> Garnish with @fresh basil{} leaves and additional @parmesan cheese{} if desired.

+<bread> Serve with @garlic bread{4%slices} on the side.
